<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/15629½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cornish,
                                        N. H.</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">29 July, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The many distressing
                            and disturbing despatches pouring in from Mexico perplex me sadly as to
                            what our immediate duty is. I note the messages you are sending to Villa
                            and indirectly to Zapata, and I suppose that they represent all that we
                            can do for the present. If <hi rend="underline">any</hi>thing else
                            should occur to you as practicable, will you not let me have the
                            suggestion to think over. I feel that a final crisis at Mexico City
                            might make more deliberate plans at any moment next to impossible.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>